# Walkthrough: Brand Palette and Layout Enhancements

I've successfully implemented the brand palette enhancements, layout modifications, and the logo component updates as requested.

## Summary of Changes

### 1. Brand Palette & [globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css)
- **Color Themes**: Added 7 brand new CSS color themes (`.theme-green`, `.theme-blue`, `.theme-yellow`, `.theme-fucsia`, `.theme-violet`, `.theme-red`, `.theme-orange`) based on the updated design system. Each theme uses refined primary and secondary HSL values for sharp contrast.
- **Base Backgrounds**: Optimized `--background` and `--card` colors in both light (`0 0% 100%`) and dark (`240 10% 4%`) modes for a cleaner canvas look.
- **Smooth Transitions**: Added `transition: background-color 0.3s ease, color 0.3s ease;` to `body` and `*` elements for a more premium feeling during theme toggling.
- **Public Layout Grid**: Integrated the dotted grid background pattern to `.layout-public-root` (`radial-gradient` overlay with `24px` spacing).

### 2. Logo Components Updates
- **Dynamic Icons**: Both [Logo](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/base/BaseNavigator.tsx#56-104) components (Public & Admin) now accept `color` and `bg` props to seamlessly switch between the full textual logo and the new square icon variations.
- **Background Logic**: Depending on the `bg` prop, the correct colored or monochrome icon is loaded into an appropriately sized and padded square container.
- **Clickable Links**: The Logo component content is now wrapped in a `next/link` component to act as a navigational shortcut back to the homepage (`/`).

### 3. Public Layout & Header Adjustments
- **Transparent Header**: Modified `.layout-header-main` in [globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css) to be fully visible and `bg-transparent`.
- **Removed Footer**: Detached `<PublicFooter />` from the public layout structure so the grid and content take up the full emphasis.

### 4. Theme and Color Selector Implementations
- **`next-themes` Verification**: Confirmed `next-themes` is actively tracking Light/Dark state in LocalStorage (in sync with `<SwitchTheme />`).
- **New `useBrandColor` Hook**: Authored a streamlined custom hook that automatically manages string states (e.g. `"green"`, `"red"`) with `localStorage` persistence, dynamically appending/removing the valid `.theme-<color>` classes on the root HTML element.
- **New `<SwitchColor />` Component**: Formatted to match the existing `<SwitchTheme />` trigger, it provides a dropdown populated with all 7 colors. You can find this right alongside the theme toggle in the public header.

You should now be able to start the development server (`npm run dev`), view the public page, select any of the 7 themes alongside toggling light/dark mode, and see changes directly persist and dynamically apply to the background and primary colors!

### 5. Post-It Aesthetics
- **Strict `Logo.tsx` Architecture**: The [Logo](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/base/BaseNavigator.tsx#56-104) components (both Admin and Public) have been refactored to be exclusively Post-It variants, completely discarding the old textual SVG layouts. They now accept explicit `icon` (to choose the colored Firebase `icon_XXX.png`), `postit` (to set the CSS background color), and `slogan` (boolean) props.
- **Rigid Square Layout**: The `Logo.tsx` enforces an absolute square dimension (`minWidth` and `minHeight` via inline styles plus the `shrink-0` Tailwind class). The top 20% contains a darker semi-transparent strip resembling glue, and the bottom right corner uses a `10% 30%` border radius curve to mimic peeling paper.
- **Icon Rendering Logic**: The actual graphic (the "S" Standlo shape with its own peeling effect provided in your Firebase assets) is centered using the `PUBLIC_ICONS_URLS` registry directly pulled from Cloud Storage.
- **`CardAuth.tsx` Overhaul**: Enabled Post-It design onto the core authentication card wrapper (`CardAuth.tsx`). Upgraded the module to a client component to cleanly integrate the `useBrandColor()` hook, directly injecting the dynamic theme color so the entire login/signup interface acts as a massive Post-It.
- **`Card.tsx` Variations**: Implemented logic where `color` props (e.g., `color="green"`, `color="blue"`) applied to a `<Card />` seamlessly inject Tailwind classes mapping to the active `.theme-X` schema.
- **`Card` Glue Headers**: Handled custom CSS cascading from `.card-post-it > .ui-card-header` within [globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css) to add the darker top section that resembles the sticky part of a Post-It pad.

## 2. Global CSS Definitions ([globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css))
- Added semantic `.ui-tools-navigator-*` classes, mapping directly from the UI requirements to proper tailored styles.
