## Bug Fix: Eliminating the Initial Blue Flash
- **Root Cause Identified:** While `useBrandColor.ts` applied `.theme-green` to the layout over time, the raw `:root` and `.dark` blocks in [globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css) were still defaulting to the original blue `--primary` colors. Changing locales triggered a NextJS structural update, momentarily stripping the JS-applied theme class before `useBrandColor`'s `useEffect` could rehydrate it, causing a rapid "flash" back to the un-themed default (`blue`).
- **Resolution:** Modified the base CSS definitions inside `:root` and `.dark` within [globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css) to natively output the **green** values by default. Now, even without a specific `.theme-[color]` utility class applied during initial SSR or transitional mounting phases, the CSS will naturally resolve to green.

## Optimization: Authentication Layout Update
- **Social Login Reordering**: Modified `CardAuth.tsx` to position the Social Login buttons (Google/GitHub) at the top of the authentication card, above the standard Email/Password form. This prioritizes faster onboarding flows as the primary choice for users.
- **Card Spacing Adjustments**: Updated the global Semantic CSS (`.ui-card-content` and `.ui-card-footer` in [globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css)) to use `1rem` padding (`p-4 pt-0`) down from `1.5rem` (`p-6 pt-0`). This ensures all cards have consistent, slightly tighter padding across the UI, while adjusting the inner spacing elements (like the `divider`) to perfectly match the layout hierarchy.

## Optimization: Sizing Semantic Classes
1. **Button Component Enhancements**: Fixed syntax errors in `cva` definition, removed `defaultVariants` to strictly mandate explicit `variant` props, updated size variants to utilize semantic classes (`ui-btn-size-*`), and implemented a dynamic fallback mechanism defaulting to the active theme (`dark` / `light`) if no explicit variant is defined.
2. **Globals.css Theme & Button Standardization**: 
    * Unified all 9 styles (`light`, `dark`, and the 7 brand colors) under a single structure. Each semantic class (e.g. `.green`, `.blue`) now implements the complete set of structural base properties (like `--background`, `--card`, `--foreground`, etc.) copying the behavior of `.dark`.
    * Extracted the 7 raw color HSL values into `:root` as `--base-[color]` variables, providing a single source of truth for all themes.
    * **Button Refinement:** Re-mapped `Button.tsx` variants (e.g., `variant="green"`) to implement `theme-green ui-btn-theme` simultaneously. Refactored `.ui-btn-theme` within [globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css) to consume `var(--primary)` and `var(--primary-foreground)`. Buttons will now flawlessly adopt their passed `theme-[color]` or naturally inherit the global document's theme.
    * Appended `py-2` to the `.ui-btn` base class to assure uniform padding across all generated buttons. 
    * Refactored CSS classes within `CardAuth.tsx` to align with the new standard (`layout-auth-card-note`, `layout-auth-card-link`, `layout-auth-card-copyright` were changed to `ui-card-auth-note`, `ui-card-auth-link`, and `ui-card-auth-copyright` respectively).
    * **Canvas Onboarding Refinement:** Fixed [CanvasOnboarding](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/canvas/CanvasOnboarding.tsx#10-85) structure to use a full-height centered layout with solid `bg-background` and `text-foreground` to prevent transparency bleeding from the canvas underneath. Raised the `z-index` to 50 and applied `pointer-events-auto` to restore interaction for the "Inizia a Progettare" button. Corrected the button's color application from the raw `className="green"` to the dynamic `variant="green"`.
    * **Middleware Route Whitelisting:** Fixed an issue where Next.js middleware (`proxy.ts`) was redirecting non-authenticated users from the [PublicCanvasPage](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/%5Blocale%5D/canvas/public/%5Buid%5D/page.tsx#7-40) (`/canvas/public`) to the login page by adding `/canvas/public` to `PUBLIC_PATHS` and whitelisting the `canvas` locale area.
    * Restyled `.ui-card-auth-copyright` to render with a dynamic `border-top` using `--current-color`, mirroring the authentic dividers.
    * Added `cursor-pointer` directly to the `.ui-btn` base class to ensure all buttons correctly trigger the hand pointer, regardless of their HTML wrapping tag.
    * **Glue Effect Centralization**: Added a dynamic `--glue` CSS variable per theme (falling back to black `0 0% 0%` in `:root`, and white `0 0% 100%` in all `.dark` and color brand themes). 
    * Refactored `.ui-btn-*[color]:hover`, `.ui-logo-glue`, and `.card-post-it > .ui-card-header` to leverage `color-mix` with the `--color-glue` variable, establishing a globally synchronized, intelligent visual translucency system without hardcoded colors.
    * Removed the Two-Step Verification note `* L'accesso richiede una verifica in due passaggi` from the `FormLogin` component entirely.
- **App Icons & Metadata Standardization**:
    - Generated missing favicon resolutions (`16x16`, `32x32`, `.ico`) and mobile device icons (`apple-touch-icon`, `android-chrome-192x192`, `android-chrome-512x512`) using `sharp-cli`.
    - Configured the root `layout.tsx` `generateMetadata` function to point directly to the public Firebase Storage URLs for all 6 generated icon formats, ensuring perfect cross-device visibility for homescreen and dock additions.

