## 11. Canvas Onboarding & Layer Experience
In the final iteration, the immersive **3D Standlo Canvas** was upgraded to provide a robust onboarding and layer-based design system:
- **Canvas Catalog Sidebar:** Introduced a new slide-out catalog on the left to browse and search parts, assemblies, and stands available for your design.
- **Layer Header UI:** Added a dedicated layer selection menu (`CanvasHeaderLayers`) directly inside the top controls, enabling switching between critical operational layers such as `appendimento`, `strutture`, `impianto`, and more.
- **Fading Inactive Layers:** Integrated an advanced wireframe and fading algorithm into [GenericPart.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/canvas/GenericPart.tsx). When a specific layer is isolated (e.g. `impianto`), all non-selected items drop to a subtle 15% opacity with disabled pointer events. This declutters the workspace during intensive domain-specific design phases.
- **Auto-Routing (PDM Layers):** Added `useCases` metadata to the base entities schema. Dragging and dropping an entity from the Catalog now deterministically maps its target `layerId` based on the active `canvasType`.
- **Guided Onboarding Tour:** Implemented `<CanvasTour />`. When unauthenticated users enter the Sandbox (`?tutorial=1`), they are met with a series of pulsing UI cards that guide them through the Catalog insertion, Tool controls, and Layer manipulation.
- **Optimistic UI & Orchestrator Backing:** Injections via the Catalog are instantly mounted in the local Zustand store for zero-latency 3D feedback, while a background AppCheck-protected Orchestrator handles the Firebase asynchronous document creation.
- **Public Sandbox Editing:** Created a safe mechanism for public read-only shares (`/it/canvas/public/[uid]`) featuring a password overlay pattern (UI facade completed) mimicking the upcoming collaborative editing controls.

